00:35:34,150 --> 00:35:34,880
Cut the crap.

838
00:35:35,230 --> 00:35:36,560
Where were you scammed?

839
00:35:36,710 --> 00:35:37,840
Send me the address.

840
00:35:42,110 --> 00:35:44,110
This photo turned out beautifully.

841
00:35:45,200 --> 00:35:46,960
You look way better on camera than I do.

842
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:50,020
Look, compared to yours,
I look like a dummy in my photo.

843
00:35:52,070 --> 00:35:52,610
Wen Wen,

844
00:35:54,190 --> 00:35:54,990
I was thinking

845
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:56,680
we should find a time

846
00:35:56,710 --> 00:35:58,760
to treat Mu to a nice meal.

847
00:36:00,190 --> 00:36:03,110
You see, we've already
got our marriage certificate,

848
00:36:03,110 --> 00:36:05,310
but we haven't shown any appreciation.

849
00:36:05,630 --> 00:36:06,590
That's not necessary, is it?

850
00:36:06,590 --> 00:36:07,850
What's not necessary?

851
00:36:08,110 --> 00:36:10,150
You've been working for him for so long.

852
00:36:10,150 --> 00:36:12,010
Shouldn't you treat him to a meal?

853
00:36:14,630 --> 00:36:15,430
What's wrong?

854
00:36:20,190 --> 00:36:21,320
Have some hot water.

855
00:36:22,940 --> 00:36:23,870
What's going on?

856
00:36:25,330 --> 00:36:26,130
It's nothing.

857
00:36:27,230 --> 00:36:29,430
I just ate too much greasy food at lunch.

858
00:36:32,230 --> 00:36:32,630
Hello?

859
00:36:33,550 --> 00:36:33,960
Guang,

860
00:36:34,590 --> 00:36:35,120
Brother.

861
00:36:35,480 --> 00:36:36,480
Pack your things.

862
00:36:36,550 --> 00:36:37,750
We're going on a trip.

863
00:36:38,150 --> 00:36:38,710
Now?

864
00:36:39,150 --> 00:36:40,440
Where... Where are we going?

865
00:36:40,440 --> 00:36:41,070
Shangyi.

866
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:41,730
Okay.

867
00:36:44,200 --> 00:36:45,930
I'm afraid I have to go on a trip.

868
00:36:46,110 --> 00:36:46,640
What for?

869
00:36:47,030 --> 00:36:49,160
It's work-related; don't pry into it.

870
00:36:49,590 --> 00:36:50,280
You...

871
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:52,370
are okay, right?

872
00:36:53,110 --> 00:36:54,310
Make sure to eat well.

873
00:36:54,420 --> 00:36:55,480
I'll be back soon.

874
00:37:06,920 --> 00:37:07,580
Good stuff.

875
00:37:08,840 --> 00:37:09,640
How is it, Qin?

876
00:37:10,190 --> 00:37:11,790
Does it meet your standards?

877
00:37:12,070 --> 00:37:12,670
Youlin,

878
00:37:16,030 --> 00:37:18,360
I've been looking around here for a while,

879
00:37:18,480 --> 00:37:20,670
and I feel like
everything was just appetizers.

880
00:37:20,670 --> 00:37:23,440
So you've been holding out
the real main course for me here.

881
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:24,360
Of course.

882
00:37:24,800 --> 00:37:26,670
Those were just appetizers.

883
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:28,880
I've saved all the good stuff

884
00:37:28,880 --> 00:37:30,150
for you at the end.

885
00:37:30,400 --> 00:37:31,020
Youlin,

886
00:37:31,440 --> 00:37:33,420
I think your artistic taste

887
00:37:33,510 --> 00:37:35,000
has indeed improved a lot.

888
00:37:35,870 --> 00:37:37,400
Especially this alms bowl.

889
00:37:38,110 --> 00:37:39,240
Everyone can see it.

890
00:37:43,660 --> 00:37:45,320
You're talented and capable.

891
00:37:46,440 --> 00:37:47,190
I feel that

892
00:37:47,190 --> 00:37:49,030
guarding this small museum

893
00:37:49,030 --> 00:37:50,490
is a waste of your talents.

894
00:37:50,960 --> 00:37:52,030
This is all I can do.

895
00:37:52,030 --> 00:37:53,760
I can't do anything else, can I?

896
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:54,830
The other day,

897
00:37:55,110 --> 00:37:55,840
in Qinchuan,

898
00:37:56,510 --> 00:37:59,640
there was a vacancy
for the Antiques Association chair.

899
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:00,950
They

900
00:38:01,510 --> 00:38:02,590
asked me, "Qin,

901
00:38:03,360 --> 00:38:04,220
who do you think

902
00:38:04,480 --> 00:38:06,840
could take on this position?"

903
00:38:08,670 --> 00:38:09,870
Without hesitation,

904
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:13,000
I said, "This position suits
Zhao Youlin perfectly."

905
00:38:15,480 --> 00:38:15,960
Qin,

906
00:38:16,190 --> 00:38:17,480
you're flattering me too much.

907
00:38:17,480 --> 00:38:19,150
I... I can't do that job.

908
00:38:20,110 --> 00:38:21,710
Are you doubting my judgment

909
00:38:21,880 --> 00:38:23,030
or doubting yourself?

910
00:38:23,030 --> 00:38:24,920
Who would dare to doubt your judgment?

911
00:38:24,920 --> 00:38:27,320
You're the benchmark in our industry,

912
00:38:27,320 --> 00:38:27,980
aren't you?

913
00:38:28,920 --> 00:38:29,590
Well, Qin.

914
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:31,140
If you think I can do it,

915
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:33,000
I'll do my best.

916
00:38:33,320 --> 00:38:34,380
I'll give it my all.

917
00:38:34,440 --> 00:38:35,880
Everyone, do you think Youlin is suitable?

918
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:36,670
Yes.

919
00:38:37,320 --> 00:38:40,030
Everyone thinks so too.

920
00:38:51,190 --> 00:38:52,120
It's connected.

921
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:53,160
Brother,

922
00:38:53,480 --> 00:38:54,690
see, isn't it?

923
00:38:56,030 --> 00:38:56,510
Look,

924
00:38:57,090 --> 00:38:58,490
I didn't lie to you, did I?

925
00:38:59,510 --> 00:39:01,970
It's the tomb of Miao Guangyi,
a Founding General of the Northern Song.

926
00:39:01,970 --> 00:39:03,170
This is his hometown.

927
00:39:03,630 --> 00:39:06,000
Many Northern Song Dynasty tombs
have been discovered here before.

928
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:07,600
They're all related to Miao.

929
00:39:07,710 --> 00:39:09,480
I've been looking for this tomb
for a long time.

930
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:11,280
If I weren't certain it was his tomb,

931
00:39:11,280 --> 00:39:13,210
I wouldn't dare to give you a price.

932
00:39:14,640 --> 00:39:16,040
Let's go inside and talk.

933
00:39:19,360 --> 00:39:20,360
Oh my goodness!

934
00:39:20,760 --> 00:39:21,840
Look.

935
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:22,670
My goodness.

936
00:39:23,950 --> 00:39:25,480
It's all built with bricks.

937
00:39:25,590 --> 00:39:27,190
Look at this structure and specifications.

938
00:39:27,190 --> 00:39:29,670
The pre-Song tombs were all
earthen pit tombs.

939
00:39:29,670 --> 00:39:31,280
If this person wasn't of high status,

940
00:39:31,280 --> 00:39:32,840
such treatment and specifications
would be impossible.

941
00:39:32,840 --> 00:39:33,470
Got it?

942
00:39:39,700 --> 00:39:40,610
What's this?

943
00:39:47,670 --> 00:39:51,800
This is the epitaph of the ancestral
Grand Military Advisor of the Nation,

944
00:39:51,960 --> 00:39:53,480
Chief of the Astro-

945
00:39:53,480 --> 00:39:56,280
Chief of the Astronomical Bureau,
Master Miao.

946
00:39:56,280 --> 00:39:57,810
No need to read the epitaph.

947
00:39:58,280 --> 00:39:59,210
You don't get it.

948
00:39:59,670 --> 00:40:00,630
This epitaph is equivalent to

949
00:40:00,630 --> 00:40:02,110
our modern-day ID cards.

950
00:40:03,710 --> 00:40:04,970
The real can't be fake,

951
00:40:05,030 --> 00:40:06,480
and the fake can't be real.

952
00:40:06,480 --> 00:40:07,810
Let's look at the goods.

953
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:09,760
How many pieces are in total?

954
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:10,490
Nine pieces.

955
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:13,280
Oh my goodness!

956
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:14,810
They're all Ru Kiln pieces.

957
00:40:16,110 --> 00:40:16,630
Look.

958
00:40:20,710 --> 00:40:23,240
There are even characters
at the bottom, see?

959
00:40:23,320 --> 00:40:25,180
Miao Xun, courtesy name Guangyi,

960
00:40:25,230 --> 00:40:27,360
is from Miaodian Town in Sheqi County.

961
00:40:27,440 --> 00:40:29,670
In the first year of Guangshun,
during the Chenqiao Mutiny,

962
00:40:29,670 --> 00:40:32,800
Zhao Kuangyin seized power
from the Later Zhou Dynasty.

963
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:34,960
He then declared the country name as Song.

964
00:40:34,960 --> 00:40:35,430
You see,

965
00:40:35,840 --> 00:40:37,440
Miao Guangyi is from
Miaodian Town, Sheqi County.

966
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:38,550
He's from this very place.

967
00:40:38,550 --> 00:40:40,320
Zhao Kuangyin bestowed this to him.

968
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:42,550
If this isn't his tomb,
whose tomb could it be?

969
00:40:42,550 --> 00:40:43,610
Feel relieved now?

970
00:40:45,070 --> 00:40:47,130
The craftsmanship is indeed not bad.

971
00:40:47,150 --> 00:40:49,150
If you hadn't overplayed your hand,

972
00:40:49,630 --> 00:40:51,110
you might have fooled someone.

973
00:40:51,110 --> 00:40:52,040
What do you mean?

974
00:40:52,920 --> 00:40:54,450
Are you saying this is fake?

975
00:40:56,000 --> 00:40:57,730
Let's not beat around the bush.

976
00:40:58,510 --> 00:40:59,240
Do you really

977
00:40:59,510 --> 00:41:01,440
want me to reveal where the fake is?

978
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:05,580
I don't think you're here
for serious business.

979
00:41:05,590 --> 00:41:07,230
You're here to cause trouble, aren't you?

980
00:41:07,230 --> 00:41:07,800
Listen,

981
00:41:08,190 --> 00:41:09,630
if you're gonna pull moves like that,

982
00:41:09,630 --> 00:41:11,000
then I'll make sure to
treat you real good.

983
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:13,480
Do you want to fight one against
three thousand or the other way around?

984
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:14,590
My men fill the entire grove.

985
00:41:14,590 --> 00:41:16,120
You won't be leaving today.

986
00:41:16,480 --> 00:41:17,540
What are you doing?

987
00:41:17,550 --> 00:41:18,150
Go ahead!

988
00:41:18,670 --> 00:41:19,320
Guang.

989
00:41:19,880 --> 00:41:20,590
Let go.

990
00:41:21,280 --> 00:41:22,340
Release your hand.

991
00:41:23,030 --> 00:41:23,510
Uncle,

992
00:41:24,110 --> 00:41:25,190
don't take it seriously.

993
00:41:25,190 --> 00:41:27,190
My brother was just joking with you.

994
00:41:27,480 --> 00:41:29,360
We didn't come here to fight today.

995
00:41:29,360 --> 00:41:30,690
We came to make friends.

996
00:41:31,320 --> 00:41:31,870
Guang,

997
00:41:32,670 --> 00:41:33,730
take out the money.

998
00:41:42,210 --> 00:41:45,440
Whether we become friends or enemies,
it's up to you.

999
00:41:50,250 --> 00:41:53,380
This sky-blue glazed plate
came from your place, right?

1000
00:42:04,110 --> 00:42:04,970
Untie them now.

1001
00:42:08,700 --> 00:42:10,400
I apologize for the discourtesy.

1002
00:42:10,400 --> 00:42:11,200
I understand.

1003
00:42:12,760 --> 00:42:13,620
Second Father,

1004
00:42:14,320 --> 00:42:15,650
I've brought them here.

1005
00:42:18,280 --> 00:42:20,140
He came in with quite an attitude.

1006
00:42:21,190 --> 00:42:22,720
What does he do for a living?

1007
00:42:23,230 --> 00:42:24,710
Just like you, Second Father,

1008
00:42:24,710 --> 00:42:28,370
we're relying on what was passed down
from previous generations.

1009
00:42:28,710 --> 00:42:30,510
Have you seen anything you like?

1010
00:42:44,110 --> 00:42:44,670
Thirty thousand.
